place.name: WICKMERE
place.gazetteerText: WICKMERE, a parish in Aylsham district, Norfolk; 8 miles WNW of North Walsham r. station. Post town, Aylsham, under Norwich. Acres, 975. Real property, £1,560. Pop., 268. Houses, 64. The manor belongs to the Earl of Orford. The living is a rectory, annexed to Wolterton. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
